article_title: Maryland Man Charged With Attempting to Provide Material Support to Islamic State
article_text:
Suspected members of the terror group Islamic State sent thousands of dollars to a Maryland man in the hopes he would use the money to launch a terror attack in the U.S., according to federal charges announced Monday.

Mohamed Elshinawy, also known as Mojoe, was charged by investigators with attempting to provide material support to Islamic State, also known as ISIS or ISIL. He was also charged with obstruction of agency proceedings...
